review. Let me make a list of issues found:\n\n1. **package-lock.json files adde
d** - The project uses pnpm (pnpm-lock.yaml exists), but this PR adds package-lo
ck.json files to apps/admin, apps/api, and packages/shared-types. This violates 
monorepo consistency.\n\n2. **API Contract (`docs/api-contracts/auth.yaml`) out 
of sync**:\n   - `LoginResponse` still has `user_id` (required) but not `is_new_
user`\n   - Missing `/api/v1/auth/me` endpoint\n   - Missing `/api/v1/auth/logou
t` endpoint\n   - This violates "契约优先" principle and the check-contract-sync
would likely fail.\n\n3. **`users` table missing `last_login_at`** - PRD US-AUTH
-2 says "登录成功后更新 `users.last_login_at` 字段". The entity and migration do
n\'t have this field, and `AuthService.login()` doesn\'t update it.\n\n4. **BDD 
step definitions are stubs** - `tests/bdd/step-definitions/auth_login.steps.ts` 
is almost entirely TODO comments. The PRD explicitly says "完整 Gherkin 用例详见
`tests/bdd/auth_login.feature`", and the exec plan says to implement step defini
tions.\n\n5. **No Mobile unit tests** - The exec plan and testing.md require Flu
tter unit tests for BLoC/Widget. No `_test.dart` files for AuthBloc or LoginPage
.\n\n6. **AuthController path issue** - The controller uses `@Controller("auth")
` but since `main.ts` has `app.setGlobalPrefix("api/v1")`, the effective path is
`/api/v1/auth`. However, the DioClient base URL is `https://api.social.world/api
/v1` and the repository uses `/auth/login` etc. So this actually matches. Wait, 
let me double check... Yes, the baseUrl is `https://api.social.world/api/v1` and
the endpoints are `/auth/login`, so the full URL is `https://api.social.world/ap
i/v1/auth/login`. And the NestJS controller path is `api/v1/auth/login`. This is
actually correct.\n\nWait, I need to re-examine the controller. In the diff, the
controller changed from `@Controller("api/v1/auth")` to `@Controller("auth")`. W
ith the global prefix `api/v1`, this results in `api/v1/auth`. So that\'s correc
t. The old code had the full path in the controller which was actually redundant
/wrong.\n\n7. **Shared Types** - I need to check if `packages/shared-types` has 
interfaces that match the DTOs. It exports from `generated/auth/src` but the `au
th.yaml` is out of sync, so the generated types are also out of sync.\n\n8. **Ra
te limiting** - The PRD mentions "登录接口增加基础速率限制：同一手机号 1 分钟内
最多请求 1 次验证码，1 小时内最多 5 次." This is not implemented.\n\n9. **`seedS
msCode` dev endpoint** - The `AuthService` has a `seedSmsCode` method but there\
's no controller endpoint exposing it for dev/testing. This makes the BDD tests 
and manual testing difficult.\n\n10. **Potential race condition in `AuthIntercep
tor`** - When `_refreshToken()` succeeds, the interceptor resolves the current r
equest and then retries pending requests. However, the current request uses the 
old `requestOptions` object, which is fine since it updates the header. But pend
ing requests are retried AFTER the current request resolves. This could be a tim
ing issue but is probably okay. More importantly, `_retryPendingRequests` doesn\
't `await` the futures, so errors might be unhandled. But this is more of a code
quality issue.\n\n11. **Mobile Login Page hardcoded strings** - The login page u
ses hardcoded Chinese strings without `intl` / `flutter_localizations` as requir
ed by `docs/design-docs/flutter.md`.\n\n12. **`AuthResponseDto` uses `@IsBoolean
()` on `is_new_user`** - The DTO is used as a return type, so class-validator de
corators on response DTOs are unnecessary but harmless.\n\n13. **Migration namin
g** - The migration class is `CreateUsersAndUserProfiles20250410000000` but the 
file is `20250410000000-CreateUsersAndUserProfiles.ts`. According to docs/design
-docs/nestjs.md, migration file naming should be `YYYYMMDDHHMMSS-Description.ts`
. The class name doesn\'t matter as much, but the file is fine.\n\n14. **JWT Gua
rd uses `jsonwebtoken` directly** - This is okay but NestJS typically uses `@nes
tjs/jwt` and `@nestjs/passport`. However, the design docs don\'t mandate a speci
fic JWT library.\n\n15. **Redis connection management** - `AuthService` and `Jwt
AuthGuard` each create their own `new Redis(redisConfig)` instance. This could l
ead to connection leaks. They should inject a shared Redis provider/module. The 
infrastructure bootstrap might have set one up. Let me check.\n\nLet me check if
there\'s a Redis module or service already.',
