LoginResponse` still defines `user_id` (optional) but lacks `is_new_user` which 
is returned by the actual API.\n   - Missing `POST /api/v1/auth/logout` endpoint
.\n   - Missing `GET /api/v1/auth/me` endpoint.\n   - Violates "契约优先" and `d
ocs/design-docs/api.md`.\n\n3. **❌ Generated types out of sync**: Because `auth
.yaml` is stale, both `packages/shared-types/src/generated/auth/` and `apps/mobi
le/lib/models/generated/auth/` are out of sync with the runtime API. `check-cont
ract-sync` would fail.\n\n4. **❌ Missing `last_login_at`**: The PRD US-AUTH-2 r
equires updating `users.last_login_at` on successful login. The `UserEntity`, mi
gration, and `AuthService.login()` do not implement this.\n\n5. **❌ BDD step de
finitions are stubs**: `tests/bdd/step-definitions/auth_login.steps.ts` is almos
t entirely `TODO` comments with no real implementation. This violates the testin
g.md requirement that BDD tests should be executable.\n\n6. **❌ No Mobile unit/
widget tests**: There are no Flutter tests (`*_test.dart`) for `AuthBloc`, `Logi
nPage`, `AuthInterceptor`, or `SecureStorage`. The generated openapi tests exist
but no custom tests.\n\n7. **❌ Rate limiting not implemented**: PRD requires SM
S rate limiting (1 min / 1 req, 1 hour / 5 req). Not implemented.\n\n8. **❌ `se
edSmsCode` dev helper unreachable**: `AuthService.seedSmsCode()` exists but no c
ontroller endpoint exposes it, making BDD/manual dev testing impossible without 
direct Redis access.\n\n9. **⚠️ Redis connection leak risk**: Both `AuthService`
and `JwtAuthGuard` instantiate `new Redis(...)` directly. There is no shared Red
is provider, which can cause connection leaks. However, the infrastructure boots
trap PR might not have established one, so this is a medium concern.\n\n10. **⚠️
`AuthInterceptor` unhandled futures**: `_retryPendingRequests` does not await `_
dio.fetch(...)` futures, so unhandled exceptions could crash the app.\n\n11. **⚠️
Mobile login page hardcoded strings**: The `LoginPage` contains hardcoded Chines
e strings (`\'欢迎使用 Social World\'`, `\'手机号一键登录\'`, etc.) without usin
g `intl` / `flutter_localizations` as required by `docs/design-docs/flutter.md`.
\n\n12. **✅ Good things to note**:\n    - DB + API + Mobile all have implementa
tions.\n    - Migration follows naming conventions.\n    - JWT Guard checks blac
klist and token type.\n    - AuthInterceptor handles concurrent refresh with a q
ueue.\n    - `docs/modules/auth.md` was updated.\n    - Global exception filter 
correctly maps HTTP codes to business codes (1000, 2000, 2001).\n\nWait, I need 
to also check if there are any issues with the `BusinessException` constructor c
hange. The diff shows it was updated to include `data: null` in the super call. 
