` now uses `message` instead of `Array.isArray(message) ? message[0] : message`.
The validation errors from class-validator might return an array of messages. If
`message` is an array, it will be stringified to something weird. Let me verify 
if this is an issue.\n\nActually, looking at the filter:\n```typescript\nmessage
= String(resObj.message || resObj.error || "Error");\n```\nIf `resObj.message` i
s an array (which happens with ValidationPipe), `String([...])` becomes `"field 
must be longer than..."` which is okay-ish but not great. The original code had 
`Array.isArray(message) ? message[0] : message`. This change loses the array-han
dling logic for validation messages. This is a regression.\n\nAlso, the `Busines
sException` is handled separately, so validation errors (HttpException with arra
ys) will now output a joined string instead of the first message. That\'s a bug.
\n\nLet me also check the `LoginPage` - it imports `social_world_design_system` 
and uses `DesignTokens` which is good. But it also uses hardcoded colors via `De
signTokens.onSurfaceColor.withOpacity(0.7)` - `withOpacity` is deprecated in new
er Flutter but probably fine. More importantly, the `TextStyle` is constructed m
anually instead of using theme text styles. But the design docs say "禁止在 page
中使用 `Color(0xFF...)` 硬编码" - it doesn\'t say you can\'t manually create Tex
tStyles if you use DesignTokens. This is borderline.\n\nActually, looking more c
arefully:\n```dart\nstyle: TextStyle(\n  fontSize: DesignTokens.fontSizeHeadline
,\n  fontWeight: FontWeight.bold,\n  color: DesignTokens.onSurfaceColor,\n),\n``
